The paper proposes a method for designing dynamical systems using deep neural networks to handle the switching and combination of multiple behaviors in a robot. The application of the proposed method is in manipulating soft materials, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves using sensory and instruction signals to switch between subtasks, which requires the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The proposed model also includes a convolutional autoencoder, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) applications. Finally, the use of deep neural networks to design dynamical systems is related to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
